title: For Sale:  Swiss K 31 Rifle
postcontent:
Arguably the most accurate of the WW2 battle rifles featuring the lightning fast, straight pull bolt action,  chambered in 7.5 X 55 mm with a 23 ½ in. barrel.  The 7.5 X 55 cartridge produces a very flat trajectory with approx.. 15-20% more muzzle energy than the standard 308 / 7.62 X 51 cartridge.  There at least four sources for this cartridge.

  If you are a collector of military firearms or a hunter looking for rifle that will take almost any North American game, the K31 would be an excellent choice for your collection.

The rifle shown below is the most accurate rifle I have ever owned.  The K31 in original condition is inherently accurate but this rifle has also been pillar bedded and receiver bedded making it capable of even tighter shot groups.  It will consistently shoot 1 MOA with Swiss GP11 surplus ammo (I have some of this for sale).

This rifle was purchased from the importer as “Excellent” grade.  It has 90%+ bluing, a bright shiny bore, a 6 round detachable magazine, and an incredibly smooth 3 ½ to 4 # trigger.

As shown, the rifle is fitted with an easily removable, no mar bipod mount and scope mount made by Swiss St. Marie, and a Bushnell 3-9 scope.  These items will be priced separately.  Please ask for prices if you are interested.

The beech stock has been respectively and lightly sanded to preserve all of the original contours and historical markings.  It has 7 coats of hand rubbed Tung Oil giving it a beautiful and tough finish.

I am asking $385 for the rifle stand alone.  I will give a package price with the items listed above if you are interested.

To see this rifle, or for more information, please contact Jim at 218-370-9258 or email mcginnis@boreal.org .

Thanks for your interest.

title: For Sale:  Swiss K 31 Rifle
postcontent:
Arguably the most accurate of the WW2 battle rifles featuring the lightning fast, straight pull bolt action,  chambered in 7.5 X 55 mm with a 23 ½ in. barrel.  The 7.5 X 55 cartridge produces a very flat trajectory with approx.. 15-20% more muzzle energy than the standard 308 / 7.62 X 51 cartridge.  There at least four sources for this cartridge.

  If you are a collector of military firearms or a hunter looking for rifle that will take almost any North American game, the K31 would be an excellent choice for your collection.

The rifle shown below is the most accurate rifle I have ever owned.  The K31 in original condition is inherently accurate but this rifle has also been pillar bedded and receiver bedded making it capable of even tighter shot groups.  It will consistently shoot 1 MOA with Swiss GP11 surplus ammo (I have some of this for sale).

This rifle was purchased from the importer as “Excellent” grade.  It has 90%+ bluing, a bright shiny bore, a 6 round detachable magazine, and an incredibly smooth 3 ½ to 4 # trigger.

As shown, the rifle is fitted with an easily removable, no mar bipod mount and scope mount made by Swiss St. Marie, and a Bushnell 3-9 scope.  These items will be priced separately.  Please ask for prices if you are interested.

The beech stock has been respectively and lightly sanded to preserve all of the original contours and historical markings.  It has 7 coats of hand rubbed Tung Oil giving it a beautiful and tough finish.

I am asking $385 for the rifle stand alone.  I will give a package price with the items listed above if you are interested.

To see this rifle, or for more information, please contact Jim at REDACTED or email REDACTED .

Thanks for your interest.

title: For Sale:  Saiga "Fully Converted" AK47 AK74 Saiga 12
postcontent:
Hi All. -----------------------------------------------------------------------
***Sellers- Please do not Mislead Buyers on this Site by Misrepresenting your Saiga's as "Converted" or "Fully Converted." Converted doesnt mean moving the trigger group forward and throwing a stock on your rifle. "Converted" or "Fully converted" means the Front sight Base (FSB) has been replaced with the correct 24mm threaded sight post. Correct Mil-Spec Gas Tube. Correct Mil-Spec Gas Port with Bayo Lugs and Cleaning Rod Holes. Also, the handguard retainer had to have been replaced and not with some die cast retainer kit that uses allen keys to install. 
A "True Conversion" will really look like a Present Day ARSENAL Made AK47/74 or the Russian Izhmash AK100 series rifles. Do what you want for your asking price... That's another story! 

****Buyers....Be smart and do your research before shelling out your hard earned money! --
Otherwise, you are buying a high priced $229 Sporterized Rifle with $100 worth of immitation parts for $700-$1300!
*Genuine Russian or Bulgarian FSB's costs about $90.
*Genuine Russian, Bulgarian, E.German AK74 muzzle Brakes $60-$75.
*Genuine Russian or Bulgarian HandGuard Retainers around $30.
*Genuine Eastern European Cleaning Rod  $10-$15.
*Genuine Russian or Bulgarian Gas Block w/Bayonet Lug $60-$70.

title: For Sale/Trade:  L3 M6X LED Tactical Laser Illuminator Pistol Laser Light for Glock
postcontent:
Please message with any questions. This model is for the Glock line of pistols. These usually sell for around $250+ This one is brand new in box and is one bad ass light, it's made by L3 that makes Eotechs. Please message with any questions. 




The M6X Tactical Laser Illuminator was built for U.S. Special Operations personnel and designed to perform under the most rigorous conditions and survive the harshest environments. Because of this, the M6X is built to go as deep as 66ft. and still remain waterproof.

The M6X utilizes a Xenon bulb that delivers a peak output of 125+ lumens and is protected by the Shock Suppression System which is designed to handle the heavy recoil demands of today’s tactical loads. Powered by two (2) 3V 123 lithium batteries (included), the M6X has a run time of one (1) hour.

The M6X utilizes a red, class III visible laser with a range of 200 meters. The laser is adjustable for elevation and windage (using the supplied tool) allowing the user to zero in the laser.

The M6X features a 4 position selector switch in conjunction with an ambidextrous rocker switch located on the removable backplate. The selector switch turns to Lock-Out, Laser Only, White Light Only or White Light and Laser combined. Once the desired output is selected the M6X is activated by using the rocker arm toggling down for Momentary On or locking up for Constant On. The rocker backplate on the M6X is interchangeable with any other backplate designed for either M3X or M6X models, giving you greater versatility of application.

L-3 Insight Technology Incorporated offers three options for mounting the M6X to your firearm. The patented Slide-Lock® system allows for instant tool-free mounting and removal by simply sliding the unit onto the rail and locking it into place with the spring-loaded latchbar. The Universal Slide-Lock mount fits most pistols and comes with two latchbars to insure the proper fit, while the 1913 Slide-Lock mount is designed specifically for the true M1913 Mil-Spec Picatinny rail and also comes with two latchbars to insure proper fit.

The Rail-Grabber™ mount fits most rail configurations whether for a pistol, rifle or shotgun. The Rail-Grabber interface utilizes a screw-adjustable locking plate that can be tightened to insure a rock solid fit. The Rail-Grabber mount is particularly recommended for heavy recoiling firearms.

Swiss Military 7.5x55 GP11 ball ammunition. This is some of the finest quality ammunition ever produced. Extremely accurate, reliable and non-corrosive. Mostly made in 1982, but possibility of other years of production. Comes 10 rounds per box, 6 boxes per brick 8 bricks per case. The Cartridge features a brass case and Berdan primers and Cupronickel jacketed bullets with lead core. Cupronickel is an alloy of copper that contains nickel and strengthening elements, such as iron and manganese and is magnetic so a magnet does stick to the bullet. Bullet weight per the importer is 174 grain.

The 174 grain Full Metal Jacket GP 11 spitzer bullet offered good aerodynamic efficiency and ballistic performance with a ballistic coefficient (G1 BC) of 0.505 to 0.514 (ballistic coefficients are somewhat debatable). At 2560 ft/s muzzle velocity the standard GP 11 ball bullet retained supersonic velocity up to 875 yards.  Even by contemporary (2007) standards 875 yards typical effective range is quite remarkable for a standard military rifle round.[2]

GP 11 is regarded as highly accurate and well-manufactured ammunition.

The EMOD is about one inch longer than the original Modstock and with the rubber butt plate installed, is about a quarter of an inch longer than the CRANE SCB. The increased length of the EMOD is a major benefit when used on scoped rifles (SPR/DMR), as it increases the available comb for any given length of pull. The buttplate of the EMOD is slightly wider and longer at the toe than the regular M4 stock with a noticeable negative pitch, making transitions from the ready feel much more natural. The EMOD was given enough weight to help balance out the normally muzzle heavy feel associated with negative pitch buttstocks. The toe of the buttplate is rolled under; giving the EMOD a superior feel when the weapon is held in the "out of pocket" heads up hold. The buttplate is covered with a removable rubber buttpad that is molded over a metal strike plate. The shape of the buttplate and the rubber buttpad give a solid stock purchase in all situations. The EMOD features more storage in the removable, waterproof side compartments; the EMOD holds up to four CR123 or three AA batteries. There is also an additional weather proof compartment in the clubfoot area of the stock, this compartment can be accessed quickly and holds two AA batteries or other small parts. Constructed from the finest materials, the EMOD will stand up to the most rugged demands. The EMOD Combo Kit is only available with the MilSpec size Receiver Extension Tube and is available in Black, Foliage Green and Flat Dark Earth (tan). title: For Sale:  Unit Match pistol, 45 ACP 1911 A1, USGI  National match parts
postcontent: Thinning my 1911 collection.  This is a match pistol ( I think a Hardball gun ), built at the unit level to shoot Bullseye matches. As near as I can tell, it was made up of Military National Match parts. The Slide, Barrel, and barrel Bushing are all marked with National Match numbers. The internals are assumed to be Colt, since Colt was the one supplying parts to the Government in the 1960s .  As was often customary at the unit level, the pistol was built on an Essex frame. The two " upsides " of the Essex frame were that the steel was of a lot better quality than a pistol built in 1945 or earlier, AND the shooter could take the pistol with him to his next duty station. ( he owned the frame, and not the Government ). This pistol is in excellent plus condition. VERY tight frame to slide fit , excellent trigger ( about 3 1/2 pounds).  This pistol was built for accuracy.  Military manual included.  Please feel free to ask questions. FTF in OK.   FFL outside OK
